  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How come people on Quora ask questions here, when they can get them on Google and why is Quora just a question/answer site, will it expand?",
  "response": "People often choose to ask questions on Quora instead of simply Googling them for several reasons:\n\n### 1. **Human Expertise and Insights**:\n   - Quora allows users to get answers directly from people with personal experience, expertise, or unique perspectives on a topic. While Google provides information from websites, Quora offers human-driven insights that can be more nuanced or relatable.\n\n### 2. **Discussion and Interaction**:\n   - Quora fosters a community where users can engage in discussions, ask follow-up questions, and even debate answers. This interaction is not possible with a simple Google search.\n\n### 3. **Tailored Responses**:\n   - Users can ask specific, detailed questions and receive personalized answers. Google might provide generic information, but Quora can address niche or context-specific queries.\n\n### 4. **Community and Trust**:\n   - Many users trust the Quora community because answers are often from verified experts or individuals with relevant backgrounds. Google, on the other hand, pulls from a wide range of sources, some of which may not be reliable.\n\n### 5. **Evolving Answers**:\n   - Answers on Quora can be updated over time as new information becomes available or as users contribute additional perspectives. Google results may not always reflect the most current or comprehensive information.\n\n### 6. **Discoverability of Related Questions**:\n   - Quora often shows related questions and answers which can help users explore a topic more deeply than a Google search might.\n\n### Why is Quora Just a Question/Answer Site?\nQuora\u2019s core function is to facilitate knowledge-sharing through questions and answers. This focus has allowed it to build a large, engaged community around its niche. However, Quora has evolved over time to include features like blogs, spaces (community forums), and monetization options for creators, which suggests it is not limited to just being a Q&A platform.\n\n### Will Quora Expand?\nQuora has already expanded beyond its original Q&A model. For example:\n- **Quora Spaces**: Communities for specific topics or interests.\n- **Quora+**: A subscription service offering access to exclusive content.\n- **Monetization for Creators**: Writers can earn money through the Quora Partner Program or by creating subscription content.\n- **AI Integration**: Quora has experimented with AI tools to assist with content creation and moderation.\n\nIts future expansion will likely depend on how it balances its core Q&A identity with new features and monetization strategies. It may continue to diversify its offerings to compete with other platforms and attract a broader audience. However, its success will hinge on maintaining the quality and trust of its community.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
